[
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-001",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 1,
    "text": "Alice was beginning to get very tired of sitting by her sister on the bank, and of having nothing to do.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-001--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-002",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 2,
    "text": "Once or twice she had peeped into the book her sister was reading, but it had no pictures or conversations in it, 'and what is the use of a book,' thought Alice 'without pictures or conversations?'",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-002--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-003",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 3,
    "text": "So she was considering in her own mind whether the pleasure of making a daisy-chain would be worth the trouble of getting up and picking the daisies, when suddenly a White Rabbit with pink eyes ran close by her.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-003--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-004",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 4,
    "text": "There was nothing so very remarkable in that, nor did Alice think it so very much out of the way to hear the Rabbit say to itself, 'Oh dear! Oh dear! I shall be late!'",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-004--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-005",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 5,
    "text": "But when the Rabbit actually took a watch out of its waistcoat-pocket, and looked at it, and then hurried on, Alice started to her feet and ran across the field after it.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-005--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-006",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 6,
    "text": "In another moment down went Alice after it, never once considering how in the world she was to get out again.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-006--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-007",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 7,
    "text": "The rabbit-hole went straight on like a tunnel for some way, and then dipped suddenly down, so suddenly that Alice found herself falling down a very deep well.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-007--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-008",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 8,
    "text": "Either the well was very deep, or she fell very slowly, for she had plenty of time as she went down to look about her and to wonder what was going to happen next.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-008--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-009",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 9,
    "text": "She looked at the sides of the well and noticed that they were filled with cupboards and book-shelves, and here and there she saw maps and pictures hung upon pegs.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-009--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-010",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 10,
    "text": "She took down a jar from one of the shelves as she passed; it was labelled 'ORANGE MARMALADE', but to her great disappointment it was empty.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-010--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-011",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 11,
    "text": "'Well!' thought Alice to herself, 'after such a fall as this, I shall think nothing of tumbling down stairs!'",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-011--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-012",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 12,
    "text": "Down, down, down—would the fall never come to an end?",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-012--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-013",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 13,
    "text": "'I wonder how many miles I've fallen by this time?' she said aloud.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-013--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-014",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 14,
    "text": "Presently she began again: 'I wonder if I shall fall right through the earth!'",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-014--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-015",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 15,
    "text": "Down, down, down, there was nothing else to do, so Alice soon began talking again.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-015--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-016",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 16,
    "text": "'Dinah'll miss me very much to-night, I should think!'",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-016--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-017",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 17,
    "text": "She felt that she was dozing off, and had just begun to dream, when suddenly, thump! thump! down she came upon a heap of sticks and dry leaves, and the fall was over.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-017--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-018",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 18,
    "text": "Alice was not a bit hurt, and she jumped up on to her feet in a moment.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-018--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-019",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 19,
    "text": "Before her was another long passage, and the White Rabbit was still in sight, hurrying down it.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-019--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-020",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 20,
    "text": "She found herself in a long, low hall, which was lit up by a row of lamps hanging from the roof.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-020--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-021",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 21,
    "text": "There were doors all round the hall, but they were all locked.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-021--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-022",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 22,
    "text": "Suddenly she came upon a little three-legged table, all made of solid glass; there was nothing on it except a tiny golden key.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-022--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-023",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 23,
    "text": "On the second time round, she came upon a low curtain she had not noticed before, and behind it was a little door about fifteen inches high.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-023--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-024",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 24,
    "text": "Alice opened the door and found that it led into a small passage, not much larger than a rat-hole.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-024--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-025",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 25,
    "text": "How she longed to get out of that dark hall, and wander about among those beds of bright flowers and those cool fountains.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-025--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-026",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 26,
    "text": "There seemed to be no use in waiting by the little door, so she went back to the table.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-026--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-027",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 27,
    "text": "This time she found a little bottle on it, and round the neck of the bottle was a paper label, with the words 'DRINK ME,' beautifully printed on it in large letters.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-027--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-028",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 28,
    "text": "It was all very well to say 'Drink me,' but the wise little Alice was not going to do that in a hurry.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-028--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-029",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 29,
    "text": "However, this bottle was not marked 'poison,' so Alice ventured to taste it.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-029--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-030",
    "unit": "alice-wonderland-ch1",
    "level": "b2",
    "order": 30,
    "text": "Finding it very nice, she very soon finished it off.",
    "audio": "/audio/alice-wonderland-ch1/alice-wonderland-1865-c1-b2-030--n.mp3",
    "tags": [
      "alice-wonderland",
      "chapter1",
      "text-only"
    ]
  }
]
